11 [EFFECTIVE UPON PASSAGE]: Sec. 8. (a) Except as provided in
12 section 4.5(d) of this chapter, if the court finds that the allegations in
13 a petition described in section 4 of this chapter are true, the court shall
14 terminate the parent-child relationship.
15 (b) If the court does not find that the allegations in the petition are
16 true, the court shall dismiss the petition.
17 (c) The court shall enter write a formal order with:
18 (1) findings of fact that support the entry of the conclusions
19 required by subsections (a) and (b); and
20 (2) any specific factors used to determine the child's best
21 interest.
22 SECTION 14. An emergency is declared for this act.
